OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FWatchdog sorry after MPs'  
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25FChristmas parties row      
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Parliament's expenses watchdog has     
OL,6, apologised for publishing advice that  
OL,7, MPs could claim for the cost of an     
OL,8, office Christmas party.                
OL,10,FThe Independent Parliamentary Standards
OL,11,FAuthority (Ipsa) faced a backlash from 
OL,12,FMPs after saying they could claim for  
OL,13,Ffestive get-togethers.                 
OL,15,FMPs on all sides rejected the guidance,
OL,16,Fwith one calling it "bonkers" amid a   
OL,17,Fcost of living crisis.                 
OL,19,FIpsa's chief executive Ian Todd said   
OL,20,Fthe body had "got the messaging wrong".
